  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with a displaced, shortened, midshaft clavicular fracture are randomized in two
      groups: conservative or operative treatment. The conservative arm is treated with a sling for
      6 weeks. The operative arm is treated with osteosynthesis, within 2 weeks.

      Patients are clinically and radiologically evaluated during 1 year. A economical analysis is
      also done.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
